Is it the head

00:23:05.120 --> 00:23:06.860
Commandery Princess Consort An
is holding?

00:23:06.920 --> 00:23:07.480
Yes.

00:23:08.039 --> 00:23:10.480
Consort Hui is truly perceptive,

00:23:10.490 --> 00:23:11.700
and godlike in solving cases.

00:23:12.079 --> 00:23:14.480
Just by looking
at the skull in someone else's hands,

00:23:14.839 --> 00:23:17.880
she could determine the deceased
was a palace staff who fell and drowned.

00:23:19.599 --> 00:23:20.240
Leng Yue.

00:23:21.119 --> 00:23:21.880
You explain.

00:23:22.300 --> 00:23:23.370
Reporting to Your Majesty.

00:23:24.200 --> 00:23:25.400
Just now, this skull

00:23:25.680 --> 00:23:26.920
suddenly jumped from the pond

00:23:26.930 --> 00:23:29.020
and was restrained
by Commandery Princess Consort An.

00:23:29.030 --> 00:23:31.120
Her Highness wanted
the palace official to handle it,

00:23:31.559 --> 00:23:34.839
but Commandery Princess Consort An
feared the cause of death was unclear

00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:37.279
and that the culprit
might still be hiding in the palace.

00:23:38.160 --> 00:23:38.680
Therefore,

00:23:39.680 --> 00:23:40.799
a dispute occurred.

00:23:42.160 --> 00:23:42.680
Your Majesty.

00:23:43.640 --> 00:23:45.559
I didn't mean to offend Consort Hui.

00:23:46.359 --> 00:23:46.920
It's just that

00:23:46.960 --> 00:23:49.440
the rest of the deceased's remains
should still be in the pond

00:23:49.450 --> 00:23:51.079
and the cause of death is still unknown.

00:23:51.559 --> 00:23:53.519
As the only coroner
in the Imperial Garden,

00:23:53.640 --> 00:23:55.119
I must prioritize the deceased.

00:23:55.640 --> 00:23:56.720
You're

00:23:56.880 --> 00:23:59.119
